getSearchCoursesList

public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getSearchCoursesList()
Method used to search the user query on the list of valid courses. Used in courses.jsp page, to search for any user specified courses. Can be used in other pages, if implemented with two variables - searchCoursesList,searchCourse. If no search is specified, it returns the entire list on which to search. So set the entire list at firt to have proper values returned. Searches for four methods - contains, starts with, equals, not blank, right now available with bbNG tags.

Returns:
the searchCoursesList - list of courses containing the search query.
See Also:
- Generic method which is called to perform the function.

searchQueryInList

private java.util.List<java.lang.String> searchQueryInList(java.lang.String query,
                                                           java.util.List<java.lang.String> listOfValues)
Method used to search the user query on the list of valid values. Generic method, which can be used in any search, if implemented with two variables - query ,listOfValues. If no search is specified, it returns the entire list - listOfValues on which to search. So set the entire list at first to have proper values returned. Searches for four methods - contains, starts with, equals, not blank, right now available with bbNG tags.

Parameters:
query - - Search query
listOfValues - - List in which to search the query for.
Returns:
listOfSearchResults - List of search results containing the query.
